00:00:10.560 --> 00:00:13.490
— 1983: The Canary Islands, Off the Northwest African Coast —

00:00:21.420 --> 00:00:22.830
W-We did it!

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:27.220
We finally pulled up the treasure chest
that sank one hundred years ago!

00:00:27.220 --> 00:00:29.020
All right! Careful now!

00:00:29.020 --> 00:00:32.640
Keep calm! Just bring it this way...

00:00:30.630 --> 00:00:32.640
I know! I know!

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:33.520
Up we go.

00:00:33.820 --> 00:00:36.900
Isn't it a bit long and narrow
to be a treasure chest?

00:00:36.900 --> 00:00:39.110
Hey! You're lifting it too high!

00:00:40.150 --> 00:00:42.160
Okay, I'm putting it down.

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:44.290
One, two, three!

00:00:45.100 --> 00:00:48.010
All right! H-Hurry up and pry it open.

00:00:48.010 --> 00:00:49.780
Wait. Th-This is bizarre.

00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:53.040
This box is locked from the inside.

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.730
Who the hell cares? Bust it open!

00:00:55.730 --> 00:00:57.970
Just hang on! There's something written on it.

00:00:59.580 --> 00:01:01.920
D-I-O... DIO.

00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:03.230
Is it a name?

00:01:03.230 --> 00:01:05.670
What the hell does it matter?!

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:07.540
The sun's going to set soon.

00:01:07.540 --> 00:01:09.960
Once it gets dark, we won't
be able to see anything!

00:01:09.960 --> 00:01:11.630
Yeah, you're right.

00:01:11.630 --> 00:01:13.690
Okay, I'll go get the blowtorch.

00:01:13.690 --> 00:01:16.820
Let's say hello to our treasure!

00:01:19.740 --> 00:01:23.320
One day, an unmanned
cabin cruiser was spotted.

00:01:24.180 --> 00:01:27.980
The boat was in perfect working order,
and there were no signs of an attack.

00:01:28.580 --> 00:01:32.820
Aboard, there were only
three half-full cups of coffee,

00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:34.240
and...

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:40.700
On deck, a steel box, which had been
opened with an acetylene torch.

00:01:40.700 --> 00:01:42.690
The box was empty,

00:01:42.690 --> 00:01:47.590
and strangely, it had two compartments,
as if designed to shelter something.

00:01:48.520 --> 00:01:51.030
It was thought to have contained treasure,

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.840
but after a few months, it was forgotten.

00:02:00.610 --> 00:02:06.130
Jotaro Kujo, 17 years old.
Height: 195 centimeters.

00:02:06.130 --> 00:02:09.240
His father is Japanese, and a jazz musician.

00:02:08.970 --> 00:02:13.570
1987: Japan

00:02:09.240 --> 00:02:11.450
He's currently on tour.

00:02:11.450 --> 00:02:14.990
His mother is an American of British descent.

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:19.000
Yes, Jotaro is definitely my son.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.910
Apparently, his friends at school call him "Jojo,"

00:02:21.910 --> 00:02:25.810
derived from the "Jo" of Jotaro and the "jo" in Kujo.

00:02:26.530 --> 00:02:27.890
That's pretty dumb!

00:02:27.890 --> 00:02:29.800
S-So...

00:02:30.360 --> 00:02:33.180
How many people did Jotaro kill?!

00:02:33.180 --> 00:02:37.420
No! Don't tell me! I don't want to hear! No!

00:02:34.850 --> 00:02:38.070
Uh, who said he killed anybody?

00:02:38.070 --> 00:02:39.570
He got into a fight.

00:02:39.570 --> 00:02:43.920
Actually, the thugs he faced were
armed with nunchucks and knives.

00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:46.180
There were four, including a former boxer,

00:02:46.180 --> 00:02:48.750
and between them, fifteen bones were broken.

00:02:48.750 --> 00:02:50.650
They all had their balls crushed, too...

00:02:50.650 --> 00:02:53.650
Ah, pardon my language...
And they were sent to the hospital.

00:02:53.650 --> 00:02:57.170
Ma'am, please make sure he learns his lesson!

00:02:57.170 --> 00:02:58.410
Okay!

00:02:58.410 --> 00:03:00.650
But the problem is what happened after.

00:03:00.650 --> 00:03:02.340
Could you copy this and pass it around?

00:03:02.340 --> 00:03:03.290
Yes, sir.

00:03:03.290 --> 00:03:05.670
Your son is quite the oddball.

00:03:08.670 --> 00:03:11.020
Come in. We'll show you the way.

00:03:11.020 --> 00:03:12.260
Thank you.

00:03:12.260 --> 00:03:14.640
Well, anyway, please take him home.

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:16.750
What? He's being released already?

00:03:16.750 --> 00:03:19.380
Well, we can't keep him forever.

00:03:20.110 --> 00:03:24.020
By the way, ma'am,
your Japanese is very good.

00:03:24.020 --> 00:03:26.270
How long have you lived in Japan?

00:03:26.270 --> 00:03:27.570
Twenty years.

00:03:27.570 --> 00:03:29.290
Ah, no wonder.

00:03:29.290 --> 00:03:30.290
Good work, gentlemen.

00:03:30.730 --> 00:03:33.340
We've had our hands full lately.

00:03:33.340 --> 00:03:36.750
There's even a waiting list for cells.

00:03:36.750 --> 00:03:38.770
Your son is just up ahead.

00:03:39.450 --> 00:03:40.540
Jotaro!

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:45.830
Jotaro, throw the ball to Mama!

00:03:46.990 --> 00:03:48.090
Very good!

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:51.540
Do your best at the sports meet tomorrow.

00:03:51.540 --> 00:03:52.280
Yeah!

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:53.840
Jotaro...

00:03:54.180 --> 00:03:57.050
Entrance Ceremony

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:56.810
We should celebrate.
What would you like to eat today?

00:03:57.450 --> 00:03:59.310
I just want to eat your cooking, Mom.

00:03:59.850 --> 00:04:02.610
Jotaro... Jotaro...

00:04:03.070 --> 00:04:05.730
Jotaro... Jotaro...

00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:07.420
Jotaro!

00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:09.730
Shut the hell up!

00:04:09.730 --> 00:04:11.820
You're so damn annoying, you bitch!

00:04:11.820 --> 00:04:15.200
Bam!

00:04:15.660 --> 00:04:17.280
Okay!

00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:22.710
JoJo's Bizarre Adventure

00:04:18.660 --> 00:04:22.710
Stardust Crusaders

00:04:22.710 --> 00:04:24.960
He's actually a very sweet child.

00:04:22.710 --> 00:04:26.560
Episode 1: The Man Possessed by an Evil Spirit

00:04:24.960 --> 00:04:27.990
He's not capable of doing something so appalling.

00:04:27.990 --> 00:04:30.140
Hey! Don't fall asleep, Kujo!

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:31.690
You're being released. Get out!

00:04:31.690 --> 00:04:34.030
What part of "go home" don't you understand?!

00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:43.700
Mom, go home.

00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:45.980
I'm not going to leave here for a while.

00:04:47.340 --> 00:04:49.460
I've been possessed by an evil spirit.

00:04:50.160 --> 00:04:52.400
I don't know what he'll make me do.

00:04:52.940 --> 00:04:56.450
Even during the fight,
it took all I had to stop it.

00:04:57.070 --> 00:04:59.630
So don't let me out of this cell.

00:05:01.290 --> 00:05:04.090
For crying out loud...
See what I'm talking about, ma'am?

00:05:04.090 --> 00:05:07.260
We're trying to release him,
but he refuses to leave.

00:05:07.260 --> 00:05:12.460
Forgive my asking, but is
your son all right upstairs?

00:05:12.460 --> 00:05:14.050
This isn't a hotel!

00:05:15.110 --> 00:05:17.070
Please! Let us change cells!

00:05:17.070 --> 00:05:18.990
He's telling the truth!

00:05:18.990 --> 00:05:21.030
There really is an evil spirit possessing him!

00:05:19.280 --> 00:05:20.670
It's terrifying!

00:05:21.030 --> 00:05:23.350
We won't do anything bad again!

00:05:22.100 --> 00:05:24.600
That's enough! Quiet down!

00:05:32.620 --> 00:05:34.470
Wh-What is that?

00:05:34.470 --> 00:05:38.700
You've been locked up!
How'd you get that in here?!

00:05:41.520 --> 00:05:42.910
I told you.

00:05:43.170 --> 00:05:44.430
It's the evil spirit.

00:05:44.950 --> 00:05:46.940
The evil spirit brings things to me.

00:05:46.940 --> 00:05:48.970 line:20%
Nokotta! Nokotta! Nokotta!

00:05:48.970 --> 00:05:52.600 line:20%
He tosses him out of the ring!
Chiyonofuji wins all fourteen matches!

00:05:48.970 --> 00:05:52.600
H-He's listening to a boombox
and reading <i>Shonen Jump</i>!

00:05:52.600 --> 00:05:55.020
H-How?! Th-This is a problem!

00:05:55.020 --> 00:05:56.260
This is a huge problem!

00:05:55.770 --> 00:05:56.820
Hold it!

00:05:57.750 --> 00:06:01.260
This might not be enough to
stop you from releasing me.

00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:04.390
I'll show you what a terror
my evil spirit can be.

00:06:05.170 --> 00:06:09.090
Just so you'll understand how
dangerous it could be to let me out.

00:06:22.430 --> 00:06:24.770
M-My gun! How?!

00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:25.870
W-We've got trouble!

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:30.230
Well? Did you guys see
my evil spirit just now?!

00:06:30.630 --> 00:06:32.240
If you didn't, then...

00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:36.300
J-Jotaro!

00:06:48.210 --> 00:06:50.530
There's someone behind me.

00:06:50.530 --> 00:06:52.570
It seems to have possessed me recently.

00:06:55.370 --> 00:06:58.580
His grandpa, Joseph, had strange powers...

00:06:58.990 --> 00:07:02.450
B-But what's happening to my son?

00:07:07.020 --> 00:07:08.950
Jotaro Kujo

00:07:09.350 --> 00:07:15.270
